  "text": "In terms of architectural organization, LPs are typically implemented as application-level callbacks (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ), each of which is in charge of manipulating the LP's state depending on the simulation event dispatched via the callback. Also, multiple LPs are typically run within a same Operating System process, referred to as simulation kernel, which is in charge of performing all the housekeeping tasks, such as determining the scheduling sequence for event processing at the various LPs.",
